views.text: With Apple Vision Pro, you have an infinite canvas that transforms how you use the apps you love. Arrange apps anywhere and scale them to the perfect size, making the workspace of your dreams a reality — all while staying present in the world around you. Browse the web in Safari, create a to‑do list in Notes, chat in Messages, and seamlessly move between them with a glance. You can even bring your Mac workflows into Apple Vision Pro wirelessly with Mac Virtual Display.

And with more pixels than a 4K TV for each eye, you can enjoy stunning content wherever you are — on a long flight or the couch at home.

views.text: Apple Vision Pro is Apple’s first 3D camera. Your existing library of photos and videos looks incredible at remarkable scale. And panoramas wrap around you — making you feel like you’re standing right where you took them. You can also take spatial videos with iPhone 15 Pro, then view them on Apple Vision Pro.

views.text: Dual-driver audio pods positioned next to each ear deliver personalized sound while letting you hear what’s around you. Spatial Audio makes sounds feel like they’re coming from your surroundings. Audio ray tracing analyzes your room’s acoustic properties to adapt and match sound to your space. And if you want to use headphones with Apple Vision Pro, AirPods Pro (2nd generation) with USB‑C offer the perfect experience, featuring Lossless Audio with ultra-low latency enabled by the H2 chip in both devices.
views.desc: <button bound_box=66,1773,1014,1776>Dual-driver audio pods positioned next to each ear</button>

views.text: A high‑performance eye‑tracking system of LEDs and infrared camerasprojects invisible light patterns onto each eye. This advanced system provides ultraprecise input without your needing to hold any controllers, so you can accurately select elements just by looking at them.
views.desc: <button bound_box=66,1773,1014,1776>A high‑performance eye‑tracking system of LEDs and</button>

views.text: External view of Apple Vision Pro highlighting the array of cameras and sensors
views.desc: <button bound_box=66,1773,72,1776>External view of Apple Vision Pro highlighting the</button>

views.text: A pair of high-resolution camerastransmit over one billion pixels per second to the displays so you can see the world around you clearly. The system also helps deliver precise head and hand tracking and real‑time 3D mapping, all while understanding your hand gestures from a wide range of positions.
views.desc: <button bound_box=66,1773,1014,1776>A pair of high-resolution camerastransmit over one</button>

views.text: Highlighting the M2 and R1 chips in Apple Vision Pro
views.desc: <button bound_box=0,1773,3,1776>Highlighting the M2 and R1 chips in Apple Vision P</button>

views.text: A unique dual‑chip design enables the spatial experiences on Apple Vision Pro. The powerful M2 chip simultaneously runs visionOS, executes advanced computer vision algorithms, and delivers stunning graphics, all with incredible efficiency. And the brand-new R1 chip is specifically dedicated to process input from the cameras, sensors, and microphones, streaming images to the displays within 12 milliseconds — for a virtually lag-free, real-time view of the world.
views.desc: <button bound_box=66,1773,1014,1776>A unique dual‑chip design enables the spatial expe</button>

views.text: Testing conducted by Apple in November 2023 using preproduction Apple Vision Pro units and software. Testing consisted of full battery discharge while performing each of the following tasks: video playback, internet browsing, spatial video capture, and FaceTime. Video playback tested in conjunction with an Environment, using 2D movie content purchased from the Apple TV app. Internet browsing tested using 20 popular websites. FaceTime tested between two Apple Vision Pro units with Personas enabled. Tested with Wi-Fi associated to a network. Battery life depends on device settings, usage, network, environmental conditions, and many other factors. Battery tests are conducted using specific Apple Vision Pro units; actual results may vary.
